WEBVTT

00:06.215 --> 00:07.216
Ah!

00:10.052 --> 00:11.846
Heather! I'm gonna...

00:11.846 --> 00:13.431
- I'm gonna get help.
- [coughing]

00:14.932 --> 00:16.434
[Ray] Heather!

00:16.434 --> 00:18.561
[coughing]

00:22.857 --> 00:25.609
[panting]

00:27.695 --> 00:30.156
[coughing]

00:30.156 --> 00:32.032
[gasping]

00:35.494 --> 00:36.829
[Natalie] Heather!

00:36.829 --> 00:40.040
Heather. Heather?

00:40.040 --> 00:41.959
Heather?
Heather, wake up.

00:41.959 --> 00:43.794
[echoing]
Heather, please wake up.

00:49.842 --> 00:52.470
[monitor beeping]

00:55.055 --> 00:56.682
Heather?

00:58.684 --> 01:01.479
[coughing]

01:01.479 --> 01:03.731
It's okay, it's okay,
it's okay, it's okay.

01:06.275 --> 01:08.444
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
I'm good.
- You're okay.

01:08.444 --> 01:11.071
You're okay. You scared me.

01:14.742 --> 01:16.744
Uh...

01:16.744 --> 01:20.080
I wish, I wish...

01:20.080 --> 01:21.707
I wish I was there.

01:21.707 --> 01:23.334
- No.
- I... I...

01:23.334 --> 01:26.629
Hey, hey...

01:26.629 --> 01:28.172
I'm glad you weren't.

01:29.965 --> 01:32.927
Heather, the-the doctors say
you could have died.

01:32.927 --> 01:34.929
They always say that.

01:34.929 --> 01:36.764
Oh, easy, easy.

01:36.764 --> 01:38.599
[coughs]

01:38.599 --> 01:40.518
Let me get the pillows for you.

01:50.069 --> 01:53.364
Uh, your-your mom took Lily to
work with her for a little bit.

01:53.364 --> 01:55.449
She told me to call her
if you woke up.

01:55.449 --> 01:59.912
- Oh, my God. Heather.
- Hey.

01:59.912 --> 02:01.622
Hey.

02:01.622 --> 02:03.541
We were so worried.

02:03.541 --> 02:06.460
God, I... I couldn't even think.

02:06.460 --> 02:09.880
I... You helped me get out.
I couldn't...

02:09.880 --> 02:12.132
- [Heather] Hey, hey, hey...
- I couldn't get to you.

02:12.132 --> 02:13.509
[Heather] It's okay,
it's okay.

02:15.261 --> 02:16.804
You saved me.

02:16.804 --> 02:20.391
Hey, hey, it's okay.

02:20.391 --> 02:22.476
Really. Really.

02:26.814 --> 02:28.691
[indistinct chatter]

02:28.691 --> 02:30.943
♪ ♪

02:30.943 --> 02:34.154
[indistinct announcement
over P.A.]

02:37.908 --> 02:38.868
[Langley] I don't understand.

02:38.868 --> 02:39.994
Were you all there
to play Panic?

02:39.994 --> 02:42.121
[Dodge] No, I wasn't
playing a game.

02:42.121 --> 02:44.915
Believe me, Sergeant,
I can think of better ways

02:44.915 --> 02:46.417
to get myself killed.

02:46.417 --> 02:47.710
Hmm.

02:51.589 --> 02:53.883
Well, I'm glad you kids
are all right.

02:53.883 --> 02:56.176
- Ma'am, can I see you
outside for a minute?
- Mm-hmm.

03:02.766 --> 03:04.393
This was a bad idea.

03:04.393 --> 03:06.770
Can you sit down?
You're kind of making me dizzy.

03:06.770 --> 03:08.898
You getting hurt too
was not part of the plan.

03:08.898 --> 03:10.566
I think we should call this off.

03:10.566 --> 03:13.068
I already told you, the fire had
nothing to do with the game.

03:13.068 --> 03:14.778
You wouldn't have been there
in the first pla...

03:18.407 --> 03:21.035
Of all the stupid places
to throw a party.

03:21.035 --> 03:23.621
I know.

03:23.621 --> 03:25.080
Hey, do you guys think
the judges will give me

03:25.080 --> 03:27.374
extra points for being the
last one to leave the house?

03:31.170 --> 03:34.089
You weren't the last.

03:34.089 --> 03:38.260
Little Bill Kelly was
squatting in the basement.

03:38.260 --> 03:40.721
Tyler found his body
before the fire broke out.

03:40.721 --> 03:42.973
His body?

03:42.973 --> 03:46.018
There was a needle
in his arm, but, uh...

03:46.018 --> 03:47.978
But what?

03:47.978 --> 03:50.189
All the evidence was burned,

03:50.189 --> 03:54.276
so the cops can't be sure if
it was the fire that killed him.

03:54.276 --> 03:55.861
- [nurse] Hi, Officer Williams.
- [Williams] Morning.

03:55.861 --> 03:57.321
Where can I find Heather Nill?

03:57.321 --> 03:58.572
[whispering]
Heather, my dad is here,

03:58.572 --> 04:00.282
and he wants to talk to you.

04:00.282 --> 04:03.619
- So say that we were
at a party, okay?
- [knock on door]

04:03.619 --> 04:05.245
There she is.

04:05.245 --> 04:07.122
Rise and shine, sleeping beauty.

04:08.958 --> 04:10.542
You were very lucky.

04:10.542 --> 04:12.211
You know, a few minutes after
Natalie found you,

04:12.211 --> 04:15.756
that whole second floor
just came down.

04:15.756 --> 04:17.716
Well, it wasn't really luck.
Um... [clears throat]

04:17.716 --> 04:19.885
I heard everyone
from the party panicking.

04:19.885 --> 04:21.887
I just got out a little
later than everyone else.

04:21.887 --> 04:23.389
Mm.

04:23.389 --> 04:25.015
Whose idea was it
to have it there?

04:27.643 --> 04:29.353
Uh... [coughs softly]

04:29.353 --> 04:30.646
Yeah, it's tradition.

04:30.646 --> 04:32.564
I guess kids have it there
every year.

04:32.564 --> 04:35.025
Come on, Heather.

04:35.025 --> 04:37.194
We're not as dumb
as y'all think.

04:37.194 --> 04:41.490
We know there's another game
being played this year.

04:41.490 --> 04:44.952
[sighs deeply]

04:44.952 --> 04:48.080
Natalie...

04:48.080 --> 04:52.584
Natalie's my daughter,
and I want to believe

04:52.584 --> 04:57.256
that she's telling me
the truth, but... [sighs]

04:57.256 --> 05:00.551
this... this is
serious business, Heather.

05:01.635 --> 05:04.513
And we're gonna be watching
y'all like a hawk from now on.

05:06.932 --> 05:08.934
♪ ♪

05:14.857 --> 05:16.358
[Cortez] I spoke to the D.A.
this morning

05:16.358 --> 05:17.860
after Little Bill's service.

05:17.860 --> 05:20.696
He said Little Bill's dad
really helped him

05:20.696 --> 05:23.073
get into office.

05:23.073 --> 05:27.453
And a lot of people have
a lot of respect for his dad.

05:27.453 --> 05:28.996
That's why he was able
to stay out of jail.

05:28.996 --> 05:31.999
Yeah, you don't serve 26 years
as the county sheriff

05:31.999 --> 05:34.168
without making a few friends.

05:34.168 --> 05:36.628
Looks like he wrapping up
with Williams.

05:36.628 --> 05:40.340
Um, Mrs. Cortez,
can I get you anything?

05:40.340 --> 05:43.427
You want some... You want some
coffee or some tea to go

05:43.427 --> 05:45.721
with you?

05:47.973 --> 05:52.561
Do you remember how many people
turned out for Jimmy's service?

05:52.561 --> 05:55.314
Yeah. We had to go
up to the high school,

05:55.314 --> 05:57.191
get some extra chairs.

05:57.191 --> 06:01.111
And even then it was
standing room only.

06:05.532 --> 06:07.367
He was a really good kid.

06:08.869 --> 06:11.747
Everyone loved him.

06:11.747 --> 06:15.209
Not everyone.

06:15.209 --> 06:16.794
[Cortez] The D.A. wants me

06:16.794 --> 06:19.755
- to charge someone
for Little Bill's death.
- Are you serious?

06:19.755 --> 06:22.591
- Those kids swear up and down
that they weren't there to play.
- I know.

06:22.591 --> 06:24.259
Kids have been partying
at the Graybill House

06:24.259 --> 06:26.261
- since we were in high school.
- Maybe so,

06:26.261 --> 06:27.638
but you know,
we have fire, we got a game,

06:27.638 --> 06:29.890
we got a bunch of kids
and a bag of bones, so...

06:29.890 --> 06:31.725
So you think the kids are lying
about the O.D.

06:31.725 --> 06:33.310
Lying or not,
makes no difference

06:33.310 --> 06:34.895
if you can't prove it, you know.

06:34.895 --> 06:37.189
The evidence is in the ashes.

06:39.650 --> 06:41.902
What are you thinking?

06:41.902 --> 06:45.114
Little Bill,
he mentioned Abby Clark,

06:45.114 --> 06:47.574
and he made it sound like
there was something that he knew

06:47.574 --> 06:48.700
that we didn't.

06:50.410 --> 06:52.788
- And?
- And...

06:52.788 --> 06:55.457
what if he did?

06:55.457 --> 06:57.918
- [goats bleating]
- [chicken clucks]

06:59.378 --> 07:03.590
Okay, so here is
what I owe you, and then,

07:03.590 --> 07:08.804
this is your, uh,
two weeks' advance. Okay?

07:08.804 --> 07:11.181
- Thank you.
- Here you go. Thank you.

07:11.181 --> 07:12.808
I was, uh, you know,

07:12.808 --> 07:14.351
I was a little concerned
about you.

07:14.351 --> 07:16.562
It's great to see that you're
up and on your feet again.

07:16.562 --> 07:18.063
Me, too.

07:18.063 --> 07:20.440
You know, I'm really
proud of you

07:20.440 --> 07:21.775
that you're starting college.

07:21.775 --> 07:24.403
A lot of the young people
around here, they...

07:24.403 --> 07:26.405
you know, I don't know,
they seem kind of lost.

07:26.405 --> 07:28.282
I don't know, it's just
a certification program.

07:28.282 --> 07:29.867
- Oh?
- You know.

07:29.867 --> 07:31.869
I mean, Longhorn State has one.

07:31.869 --> 07:35.622
It's only, like, two years,
and it's pretty cheap, so...

07:35.622 --> 07:37.541
It's accounting, and...

07:37.541 --> 07:39.835
Accounting?

07:39.835 --> 07:42.129
I don't picture you
as an accountant.

07:42.129 --> 07:44.006
You're the creative type.

07:44.006 --> 07:45.966
I see you.
I watch you.

07:45.966 --> 07:49.303
You're always scribbling in that
little notebook of yours

07:49.303 --> 07:51.263
every time you get a break.

07:51.263 --> 07:53.807
I... I... Yeah, I don't know.

07:53.807 --> 07:57.019
That's just kind of to
get the stories out of my head.

07:57.019 --> 08:00.272
- You know?
- Yeah. So, why accounting?

08:00.272 --> 08:01.899
Well...
[sighs]

08:01.899 --> 08:04.902
Okay, I like... I like
writing stories,

08:04.902 --> 08:09.156
but... I don't know,
they're made up, and...

08:09.156 --> 08:11.992
in the real world,

08:11.992 --> 08:15.370
you kind of have to be
realistic.

08:15.370 --> 08:18.248
Oh... realistic.

08:18.248 --> 08:20.334
Yeah, the-the trouble with that
is everybody's got

08:20.334 --> 08:22.961
their own idea about
what realistic means.

08:22.961 --> 08:27.007
And most of those ideas,
they're made up.

08:27.007 --> 08:29.676
Make your own reality, kid.

08:36.016 --> 08:38.018
♪ ♪

08:49.613 --> 08:52.115
Come on, Lilybug, talk to me.

08:57.371 --> 08:58.956
Okay.

09:00.290 --> 09:04.044
Are we poor?

09:04.044 --> 09:05.671
Nick Derrick said that
I don't have a phone

09:05.671 --> 09:08.215
because we can't afford one.

09:10.342 --> 09:13.011
Well, that's not why
you don't have a phone.

09:15.389 --> 09:18.725
He said that's why I only have
one pair of sneakers,

09:18.725 --> 09:20.978
and why we live in a trailer.

09:23.105 --> 09:25.065
He said we were trailer trash.

09:32.614 --> 09:36.076
First off, you love
those sneakers.

09:36.076 --> 09:38.787
And second...

09:38.787 --> 09:43.041
this Nick Derrick guy,
he sounds like trash.

09:43.041 --> 09:46.128
Look, money doesn't make you

09:46.128 --> 09:48.922
who you are. Okay?

09:48.922 --> 09:52.718
You either are a garbage person
or you're not.

09:52.718 --> 09:55.679
And Nick Derrick,

09:55.679 --> 09:57.347
he sounds like a trash heap.

10:02.102 --> 10:04.146
Let's go, come on.

10:08.066 --> 10:11.236
Uh, I finally tracked down
Cole Horn.

10:11.236 --> 10:13.488
He's the player that had enough
points to go up against Jimmy.

10:13.488 --> 10:15.198
Ah, that's right.

10:15.198 --> 10:17.701
Cole's been down in Corpus
this whole time, man.

10:17.701 --> 10:18.952
Did you get a name
of his replacement?

10:18.952 --> 10:21.455
Mm-hmm, girl named
Shay O'Reilly.

10:21.455 --> 10:23.373
I tracked her down. She's
a stripper in Trinity Falls.

10:23.373 --> 10:25.584
I'm gonna get over there
to question her.

10:25.584 --> 10:27.502
But guess what else I learned.

10:27.502 --> 10:29.796
Do you remember
how Hunt said that Cole

10:29.796 --> 10:31.506
dropped out of the game,
skipped town,

10:31.506 --> 10:33.008
- met a girl online?
- Right.

10:33.008 --> 10:34.885
Well, Hunt got that wrong, too.

10:34.885 --> 10:37.095
Cole admitted that
he dropped out of the game

10:37.095 --> 10:38.889
because he got a payout.

10:40.098 --> 10:41.266
"A payout"?

10:41.266 --> 10:42.267
From who?

10:42.267 --> 10:45.062
Luke Hall.

10:46.813 --> 10:48.815
Luke Hall, huh?

10:53.362 --> 10:54.988
Hey, Bo, what's up?

10:54.988 --> 10:56.698
- Hey.
- What'd they ring you in for?

10:56.698 --> 10:58.367
This time?

10:58.367 --> 11:01.078
Have a few beers, man, they'll
get you for driving intoxicated.

11:01.078 --> 11:03.455
You know, you have an argument
with your old lady?

11:03.455 --> 11:05.415
Man, they'll haul you in
on domestic.

11:05.415 --> 11:07.459
Even if she's the one throwing
the fucking plates at your head.

11:07.459 --> 11:09.378
- [laughs] Shit.
- How about you?

11:09.378 --> 11:11.963
No, no, this time
I'm just here on pleasure.

11:11.963 --> 11:13.840
Registering for the demo derby.

11:13.840 --> 11:16.259
Yeah, popped in to say hey to
my cousin. He's a clerk here.

11:16.259 --> 11:17.844
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

11:17.844 --> 11:20.138
What are the odds he could lose
my charges down a toilet?

11:20.138 --> 11:21.473
[both laugh]

11:21.473 --> 11:23.475
You know, it's funny
you should mention odds.

11:23.475 --> 11:26.103
By any chance, you a, uh...

11:26.103 --> 11:27.854
gambling man?

11:32.234 --> 11:34.277
[Heather] We haven't heard from
the judges in, like, a week.

11:34.277 --> 11:36.696
I know.

11:36.696 --> 11:39.199
Natalie, if they call off
the game, we're fucked.

11:39.199 --> 11:41.034
Well, you want to keep playing?

11:41.034 --> 11:42.744
Well, I don't want
to stay in Carp.

11:42.744 --> 11:45.497
You know, I want to apply
to real college.

11:45.497 --> 11:47.499
And I want to...

11:47.499 --> 11:48.750
[exhales]

11:48.750 --> 11:50.419
I want to have a dorm room.

11:50.419 --> 11:53.088
And a roommate
from a different state.

11:53.088 --> 11:55.090
And I-I want,
I want to see people

11:55.090 --> 11:57.050
that I haven't seen every day
of my fucking life.

11:57.050 --> 11:58.969
You don't need Panic
to go to college.

11:58.969 --> 12:01.555
No, you don't need Panic
to go to college.

12:02.806 --> 12:04.349
I'm poor, remember?

12:08.603 --> 12:11.022
Do you remember in eighth grade

12:11.022 --> 12:12.691
when April was,
like, freaking out

12:12.691 --> 12:14.192
because I was wearing
Adam's sweatshirt

12:14.192 --> 12:15.694
and she thought I was,
like, hooking up with him?

12:15.694 --> 12:16.903
Yeah.

12:19.698 --> 12:22.200
He had donated it to Goodwill.

12:22.200 --> 12:24.661
And that's how I had it.

12:24.661 --> 12:28.415
And then I just made him swear
not to tell anyone anything.

12:29.708 --> 12:32.127
Why would you do that?
She gave you shit for weeks.

12:32.127 --> 12:33.712
Because it was better
than people knowing

12:33.712 --> 12:35.422
that I never get
the first pick of anything.

12:35.422 --> 12:37.048
Heather.

12:42.971 --> 12:45.974
[light classical music playing]

12:47.767 --> 12:50.604
I saw the D.A. the other day.

12:50.604 --> 12:52.481
Walked over to
the sheriff's office with him

12:52.481 --> 12:54.483
after the funeral.

12:55.942 --> 12:58.445
He's gonna need to arrest
someone for Little Bill's death.

13:01.573 --> 13:03.575
Cortez has got it in his head

13:03.575 --> 13:06.661
you might be mixed up
in all this Panic stuff.

13:06.661 --> 13:10.332
Of course I told him
you would never be so stupid.

13:10.332 --> 13:13.502
Told him you would never
embarrass me like that.

13:13.502 --> 13:15.045
After everything
I've worked for,

13:15.045 --> 13:16.463
everything I've done for you.

13:16.463 --> 13:18.298
This might come
as a surprise to you, Dad,

13:18.298 --> 13:20.175
but not everything's about you.

13:20.175 --> 13:21.426
Oh, you're trying to be cute?

13:21.426 --> 13:23.428
Just factual.

13:25.013 --> 13:27.474
[tires screech]

13:27.474 --> 13:28.892
Aah!

13:31.144 --> 13:32.562
Get it together.

13:34.523 --> 13:36.399
Look out there.

13:36.399 --> 13:38.026
On the hill.

13:40.278 --> 13:43.615
You see all those houses
in the trees?

13:43.615 --> 13:45.450
You see all those windows?

13:45.450 --> 13:47.452
Those are eyes, son.

13:47.452 --> 13:49.412
Watching for us to mess up.

13:49.412 --> 13:51.414
You understand?

13:53.875 --> 13:56.962
- [Natalie] So crazy.
- [Dayna laughs]

13:56.962 --> 13:58.964
- [Natalie] That's insane.
- He was really good.

13:58.964 --> 14:01.007
[quiet chatter]

14:01.007 --> 14:02.467
He gets really close though.

14:02.467 --> 14:04.469
[Natalie] That's insane.

14:06.263 --> 14:08.265
[horses neighing]

14:11.935 --> 14:13.228
- Hey.
- Hey.

14:13.228 --> 14:14.604
- Hi.
- What ya doing here?

14:14.604 --> 14:16.314
Uh, Dot said you hadn't been in

14:16.314 --> 14:17.649
for the past few days,
so I thought

14:17.649 --> 14:19.609
I'd, uh,
see how you were feeling.

14:19.609 --> 14:21.695
- Hmm.
- And, um...

14:21.695 --> 14:23.655
I got you something.

14:23.655 --> 14:25.532
I wrapped it myself.

14:28.910 --> 14:31.413
I thought I'd help him
get settled in.

14:31.413 --> 14:33.415
[Natalie laughs]

14:35.542 --> 14:37.544
[Natalie] Wow.

14:41.840 --> 14:43.842
Told you there's
not much to see.

14:45.927 --> 14:47.178
Ah, gray, gray,

14:47.178 --> 14:50.015
gray, black, black.

14:50.015 --> 14:52.892
You do know there are
other colors?

14:52.892 --> 14:54.978
I've heard rumors.

14:54.978 --> 14:56.479
It's like a monastery in here.

14:56.479 --> 14:58.231
Maybe I'm atoning for something.

14:58.231 --> 14:59.608
Are these yours?

14:59.608 --> 15:01.234
Some of them, yeah.

15:01.234 --> 15:03.737
Some of them are my dad's.

15:03.737 --> 15:06.197
Whoa.

15:06.197 --> 15:08.575
Yeah, I was, um...

15:08.575 --> 15:10.660
what, 16 when I got that,

15:10.660 --> 15:13.663
after I beat his time.

15:13.663 --> 15:15.540
Never forget
the look on his face

15:15.540 --> 15:17.417
after I came out
of the pit that day.

15:17.417 --> 15:20.003
- Well, he must have been proud.
- Not really.

15:20.003 --> 15:22.005
He was drunk.

15:24.299 --> 15:26.259
That was the last day
I saw him actually alive.

15:30.013 --> 15:33.141
Anyway, he, um... I don't know.

15:33.141 --> 15:35.185
He came back

15:35.185 --> 15:38.355
a few months later after that.

15:38.355 --> 15:40.357
And he hung himself.

15:42.567 --> 15:44.027
- I...
- We always used to joke that,

15:44.027 --> 15:46.071
you know, he'd, he would die

15:46.071 --> 15:47.781
with a bull rope in his hand.

15:47.781 --> 15:49.949
- I'm sorry, that's a...
- No, no.

15:49.949 --> 15:51.660
I shouldn't have said anything.
I shouldn't...

15:51.660 --> 15:53.203
No, I'm... that was...

15:53.203 --> 15:54.996
- I shouldn't have said
anything.
- No.

15:54.996 --> 15:56.164
You were fine, you were fine.

15:56.164 --> 15:57.457
That was...

15:57.457 --> 15:59.834
That's awful.

16:09.969 --> 16:12.681
